9 RURAL RESIDENCY MEDICAL EDUCATION TRAINING FUND
10 SECTION 3.12.(a) Part 3 of Article 1 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is
11 amended by adding the following new section to read:
12 "§ 116-36.10. Rural Residency Medical Education and Training Fund.
13 (a) Fund Established. – There is established the Rural Residency Medical Education and
14 Training Fund (Fund) as a nonreverting special fund to support training and residency programs
15 at medical schools and health affairs programs operated by constituent institutions of The
16 University of North Carolina, including the medical schools and health affairs programs at East
17 Carolina University and the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. The Fund shall consist
18 of funds appropriated by the General Assembly.
19 (b) Administration. – The University of North Carolina System Office shall administer
20 the Fund."
21 SECTION 3.12.(b) Notwithstanding any provision of S.L. 2023-134 or the
22 Committee Report referenced in Section 43.2 of that act to the contrary, The University of North
23 Carolina System Office shall allocate to the Rural Residency Medical Education and Training
24 Fund established pursuant to G.S. 116-36.10, as enacted by this section, all funds that were
25 appropriated to the Board of Governors pursuant to S.L. 2023-134 for the Rural Residency
26 Medical Education and Training Fund established by the Board of Governors of The University
27 of North Carolina pursuant to that act.
28 SECTION 3.12.(c) This section becomes effective June 30, 2025.
