42 "SECTION 9D.19A.(a) Notwithstanding G.S. 108D-65(6)b., for the prepaid health plan
43 capitated contracts required under Article 4 of Chapter 108D of the General Statutes, the
44 reimbursement for the ingredient cost for covered outpatient drugs and the professional drug
45 dispensing fee shall be set at one hundred percent (100%) of the Medicaid pharmacy
46 fee-for-service reimbursement methodologies in Attachment 4.19-B of section 12 of the
47 Medicaid State Plan under Title XIX of the Social Security Act Medicaid Assistance Program,
48 as filed with, and approved by, the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services. The National
49 Average Drug Acquisition Cost (NADAC), when applicable and as allowed under the Medicaid
50 State Plan, plus a professional dispensing fee based on the cost of the dispensing study conducted
51 on behalf of the North Carolina Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Health
