19 DIVISION OF ACCOUNTABILITY, VALUE, AND EFFICIENCY
20 SECTION 7.7.(a) This section shall be known as "The Division of Accountability,
21 Value, and Efficiency (DAVE) Act."
22 SECTION 7.7.(b) The State Auditor shall establish a Division of Accountability,
23 Value, and Efficiency (Division) within the Department of the State Auditor. The powers and
24 duties of the Division shall be to effectuate the assessment and recommendations required by this
25 section, and the State Auditor shall organize and administer the Division in such a manner as the
26 State Auditor may deem necessary to conduct the Division's work accordingly.
27 SECTION 7.7.(c) No later than October 1, 2025, every State agency shall report to
28 the Division both of the following:
29 (1) An explanation of how the agency, including each division or office within
30 that agency, utilizes public monies to execute its powers and duties under law.
31 (2) A description of all positions within that agency that have remained vacant for
32 six months or more as of the effective date of this section. The description
33 shall include the original position vacancy dates, the dates of any postings or
34 repostings of the positions, and an explanation for the length of the vacancies.
35 SECTION 7.7.(d) The Division shall assess the continued need for each State agency
36 and the vacant positions within each agency. The assessment shall be based on a review of the
37 reports submitted pursuant to this section and any other information the Division deems relevant.
38 In gathering and assessing relevant information, the Division may consult with the Joint
39 Legislative Commission on Governmental Operations. The Division may also employ
40 individuals to utilize artificial intelligence and other appropriate tools for the purpose of
41 examining any of the following with respect to State agencies and their budgets:
42 (1) Amounts spent, including the entities receiving funds and the intended
43 purpose of the amounts spent.
44 (2) The effectiveness of any amount spent in achieving the intended purpose of
45 that spending.
46 (3) Duplicative spending.
47 (4) Any other factor demonstrating the fiscal soundness or effectiveness of the
48 State agency or lack thereof.
49 SECTION 7.7.(e) No later than December 31, 2025, the Division shall report the
50 results of the assessment conducted pursuant to this section to the General Assembly. The
51 Division's report shall include, at minimum, recommendations on both of the following:
House Bill 125-Third Edition Page 23

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Any State agencies, or any divisions or offices within a State agency, that
2 should be dissolved based on the Division's assessment.
3 (2) Any State agency positions that should be eliminated based on the Division's
4 assessment.
5 SECTION 7.7.(f) The Division, in its discretion, may annually require any or all
6 State agencies to submit a report with the information required by this section, may reassess this
7 information on an annual basis in accordance with this section, and may report the results of the
8 assessment to the General Assembly.
9 SECTION 7.7.(g) Subsections (a) through (g) of this section are effective when they
10 become law and expire December 31, 2028, at which time the Division shall terminate.
