12 "§ 58-78A-18. Emergency Training Center tuition waivers.
13 (a) Registration Fees. – The Office of the State Fire Marshal shall charge State
14 registration fees for advanced fire and rescue courses delivered by the Office of the State Fire
15 Marshal at the North Carolina Emergency Training Center. The State registration fee charged
16 shall equal the tuition amount set pursuant to G.S. 115D-39 for equivalent community college
17 courses.
18 (b) Allowed Tuition Waivers. – The Office of the State Fire Marshal may waive State
19 registration fees for advanced fire and rescue courses delivered by the Office of the State Fire
20 Marshal at the North Carolina Emergency Training Center for all of the following individuals,
21 entities, and members of those entities:
22 (1) Volunteer fire departments located within North Carolina.
23 (2) Municipal, county, or State fire departments located within North Carolina.
24 (3) Emergency medical services or rescue and lifesaving departments located
25 within North Carolina.
26 (4) Fire, emergency medical services, or rescue and lifesaving entities serving a
27 lake authority that was created by a North Carolina county board of
28 commissioners prior to July 1, 2012.
29 (5) The Eastern Band of Cherokee Indians fire, emergency medical services, or
30 rescue and lifesaving tribal government departments or programs.
31 (6) Firefighters, emergency medical services personnel, law enforcement
32 personnel, and rescue and lifesaving personnel whose duty station is located
33 on a military installation within North Carolina.
34 (7) Law enforcement personnel employed by departments located within North
35 Carolina.
36 (8) High school students at schools located within North Carolina.
37 (c) Fees. – The Office of the State Fire Marshal may charge additional fees to cover the
38 costs of textbooks, supplies, and other expenses incurred in the delivery of courses or the
39 operation of the North Carolina Emergency Training Center.
40 (d) Annual Report. – Annually by February 1 of each year, the Office of the State Fire
41 Marshal shall report to the Joint Legislative Education Oversight Committee and the Joint
42 Legislative Oversight Committee on General Government on the number and type of waivers
43 granted pursuant to subsection (b) of this section."
44 SECTION 7.18.(b) Funds shall be provided to the Office of the State Fire Marshal
45 (OSFM) based on the number of full-time equivalent (FTE) students enrolled in advanced fire
46 and rescue courses delivered by OSFM at the North Carolina Emergency Training Center for
47 whom State registration fees are waived in accordance with G.S. 58-78A-18(b). OSFM shall
48 calculate FTE enrollment in the same manner as community colleges. Funds provided pursuant
49 to this subsection shall be (i) based on the equivalent tier-value for community college instruction
50 and (ii) in the same manner as funds are provided to community colleges based on the number
51 of FTE students enrolled in courses for which tuition and registration fees are waived in
