8 (3) Sections 39.16, 39.17, and 39.18 of S.L. 2023-134, and Section 39.15 of S.L.
9 2023-134, as amended by Section 8.2 of S.L. 2024-1, shall remain in effect,
10 notwithstanding any limitation to the 2023-2025 fiscal biennium.
11 (4) Public school employees paid on the teacher salary schedule, the principal
12 salary schedule, or any other salary schedule established by State law are
13 authorized to move up or down on applicable salary schedules and receive
14 applicable automatic step increases.
15 (5) Bonuses are authorized for teachers and principals pursuant to the
16 requirements of Section 7A.3 of S.L. 2023-134 and Section 1.3 of S.L.
17 2024-39, notwithstanding any limitation to the 2023-2025 fiscal biennium.
18 (6) Supplemental funds for teacher compensation are authorized pursuant to the
19 requirements of Section 7A.4 of S.L. 2023-134, as amended by Section 1.7B
20 of S.L. 2024-39, notwithstanding any limitation to the 2023-2025 fiscal
21 biennium.
22
23 ALLOW IMPLEMENTATION OF SALARY ADJUSTMENTS
24 SECTION 9.4. Notwithstanding G.S. 143C-5-4(b)(5), a State agency may
25 implement salary adjustments during the period of continuing budget authority that begins July
26 1, 2025, within its authorized recurring personal services appropriations if all of the following
27 requirements are met:
28 (1) Total personal services expenditures do not exceed the agency's authorized
29 personal services appropriation for the most recent completed fiscal year.
30 (2) Any salary increases are funded through position vacancies, turnover savings,
31 or reallocation within the personal services budget.
32 (3) The salary increases do not include scheduled salary increases based on
33 experience-based salary schedules.
34
35 USE OF FUNDS APPROPRIATED FOR EMPLOYEE BENEFITS
36 SECTION 9.5.(a) The Office of State Budget and Management shall ensure that the
37 appropriations made by this act for employee benefits are used only for those purposes.
38 SECTION 9.5.(b) If the Director of the Budget determines that funds appropriated
39 to a State agency for employee benefits exceed the amount required by that agency for those
40 purposes, the Director may reallocate those funds to other State agencies that received
41 insufficient funds for employee benefits.
42 SECTION 9.5.(c) Funds appropriated for employee benefit increases may not be
43 used to adjust the budgeted salaries of vacant positions, to provide salary increases in excess of
44 those required by the General Assembly, or to increase the budgeted salary of filled positions to
45 the minimum of the position's respective salary range.
46 SECTION 9.5.(d) Any funds appropriated for employee benefits in excess of the
47 amounts required to provide for employee benefits shall be credited to the Pay Plan Reserve.
48 SECTION 9.5.(e) No later than May 1, 2026, the Office of State Budget and
49 Management shall report to the Fiscal Research Division on the expenditure of funds for
50 employee benefits under this Part. This report shall include at least the following information for
51 each State agency:
House Bill 125-Third Edition Page 37

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) The total amount of funds that the agency received under this Part for
2 employee benefits.
3 (2) The total amount of funds transferred from the agency to other State agencies
4 pursuant to subsection (b) of this section. This section of the report shall
5 identify the amounts transferred to each recipient State agency.
6 (3) The total amount of funds used by the agency for employee benefits.
7 (4) The amount of funds credited to the Pay Plan Reserve.
